title: Integral of motion
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$\Phi^t(x)$$ be the flow of a dynamical system $$\dot{x}=f(x).$$ on $$U.$$ A functon $$F\colon U \to \R$$ is called an //integral of motion// (also //conserved quantity, first integral,// deutsch //Bewegungsintegral, Erhaltungsgröße, Erhaltungssatz//) if $$F(\Phi^t(x)) = F(x)\ \forall t\in\R \iff \L_f F = 0.$$

For discrete time dynamical systems: $$F(\Phi^n(x)) = F(x)\ \forall n \in \Z \iff F \circ \Phi = F.$$